Notes From https://learn.chef.io/tutorials/learn-the-basics/rhel/aws/set-up-a-machine-to-manage/

Setup an AWS instance and deploy local Chef Client/Dev Kit

1a. Create security group create Allow rules for ports 80/443/22 from your <WAN.IP>/32

1. Create an EC2 instance in AWS
CentOS 7 on Amazon Web Services
Region: us-east-1
AMI ID: ami-6d1c2007
Instance type: t2.micro
Assign the machine an EIP or Public IP
Use the Security group created from step 1a 
Select your SSH key or create one 

3. SSH into your newly created EC2 instance from Step 1
SSH to your Linux Test server
ssh -i /path/to/your/ec2/key centos@<Instance EIP/Public IP>

4.Install Chef Dev Kit on LInux Test Server
From the SSH prompt run the below command
curl https://omnitruck.chef.io/install.sh | sudo bash -s -- -P chefdk -c stable -v 0.16.28
